<section id="limitations">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <details class="panel limit-box">
      <summary>
        <span class="limit-title">What this paper does not claim</span>
        <span class="limit-toggle">+</span>
      </summary>
      <div class="limit-content">
        <div class="limit-grid">
          <div class="limit-item">
            <h4>Not within-person longitudinal</h4>
            <p>Repeated cross-sections, not a cohort tracked over time. Phase comparisons describe population-level shifts, not individual trajectories.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="limit-item">
            <h4>Edges ≠ causal direction</h4>
            <p>Conditional dependencies from cross-sectional data. They do not imply that one symptom causes another.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="limit-item">
            <h4>Policy associations are exploratory</h4>
            <p>Macro-level analyses linking symptoms to policy variables are hypothesis-generating, not confirmatory.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="limit-item">
            <h4>Domain mapping is interpretive</h4>
            <p>The four-domain alignment is a fixed interpretive layer for cross-phase comparability, not an ontological claim.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

